column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Grinding Sectors -  It can be beneficial to stay in a Sector for as long as possible to improve the ship since each Sector is increasingly difficult.
It seems the crew did not survive the assault. You take what you can from the remains of the ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
With the pirates gone you signal the station. We appreciate what you've done, but there'll just be another ship looking to profit from our isolation soon enough. Sorry we can't give you more.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
With the pirate ship destroyed, your ship's system is restored to full functionality. You salvage what you can from the debris.
The space station here has a traveling merchant who shows you his wares.

column11: They shut off communications, but you can tell they have begun an evacuation procedure.
A ship engineer has set up a small shop here.
column12: System: medbay, teleporter, mind, Augment: ION ARMOR, O2 MASKS, BACKUP DNA,

column11: A brief exploration yields nothing of interest.
As soon as you arrive a small Mantis ship detaches from a wreck and jumps away. You must have interrupted their salvage operation because you find a weapon ready to be installed!
The Rock people have a particularly aggressive stance toward alien races trespassing in their space. You should tread carefully here.
No one bothers your ship as you float among numerous space stations and mining platforms. The Rock certainly run efficient operations.
Carefully guided from the bridge, your beam drone removes the mine's grappling arms and sends it drifting off into space, where you shoot at it until it detonates at a safe distance.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
It seems the crew did not survive the assault. You take what you can from the remains of the ship.
You receive a hail on Federation frequencies: You're Federation?! We- we weren't sure we'd ever see a friendly face again. There's little business here, perhaps you'd like to trade?
column12: System: medbay, teleporter, mind, Weapon: LASER HULL 1, LASER CHARGEGUN 2, BEAM 2,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You cross paths with a Rock ship returning from a rare diplomatic mission. Equally surprising, the captain responds to your hails and agrees to a mutual trade.
column12: Drone: BATTLE, REPAIR, COMBAT 1, Augment: FLEET DISTRACTION, SCRAP COLLECTOR, BATTERY BOOSTER, System: medbay, cloaking, mind,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You see a Zoltan merchant and ask about his wares. He responds, Sorry, but it took years to gain their trust. I can't be seen communicating with you. I hope you understand. He cuts communications.
The slave ship is destroyed. They won't continue their evil trade, but many lives were probably lost on that ship.
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You find a pirate ship, damaged and abandoned. You salvage what you can and move on.
The Engi can do remarkable things with just a pile of scrap. The Engi hive at this beacon are selling equipment for just that.
column12: System: teleporter, cloaking, mind, Weapon: LASER CHARGEGUN 2, LASER CHAINGUN 2, ION 1,

column11: Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
Engi can't feel fear, so they bear you no ill will when you explain you're unwilling to help. They set off on their journey and you do the same.
You succeed in preventing them from being entirely destroyed, but your ship took a number of hits in the process. They offer some of the scrap and fuel they were mining out of the asteroid as thanks.

Even though each individual Engi is made up of trillions of nano-machines, their culture still revolves around traditional social interactions. A nearby station seems to be constructed for entertainment of passing Engi travellers.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
An Engi ship hails: Engine upgrade necessary for travel home. Sale of equipment necessary for engine upgrade.
column12: System: teleporter, cloaking, hacking, Drone: SHIP REPAIR, DRONE SHIELD, COMBAT FIRE, Weapon: MISSILES 3, BOMB FIRE, BOMB 1, Augment: BATTERY BOOSTER, BACKUP DNA, SCRAP COLLECTOR,

column11: A few years ago this region was bustling with trade activity. Now it is overrun with bandits and marauders. You should tread lightly here.
You try your best but one stray rock hits a key structure in their ship. It breaks apart in front of your eyes. You salvage what you can before leaving, and try not to think about the lost crew.

You see a small station nearby and feel the shudder of shots ringing through the ship. You can't be sure without sensors, but it seems there may be intruders on the ship! They must have a Super Shield bypass unit; boarders are on board!
You feel naked without functioning sensors. You half expect a Rebel ship to appear from behind a cloud at any moment, but none come.
You get lucky and find them floating not too deep into the nebula. Thrilled to be found by friendlies, they come on board and abandon their wrecked ship.
With the sensors down, you spend a good deal of time staring out the window. It is, you must admit, rather beautiful here.
You thank them but prepare to move on.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

A few small ships are visible on the vidscreen, and you almost activate weapons targeting. However, sensors indicate they are simply honest merchants. The pirates must be making you jumpy. You message them asking about their wares.

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
Once the Federation forces were scattered, the Rebels came down hard on the locals here. Between the 'tax collectors' and military bases, the Rebel presence in this sector is high.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You receive generic advertisements from a nearby public ship-yard. It seems they are willing to work on any ship, not only those of Rebel hue.
